One person has died and nine other injured after a delivery vehicle lost control and rolled on the R556, Modikwe Rustenburg on Christmas morning. According to Netcare 911, one of the surviving passengers was in a critical condition and had had to be airlifted by helicopter to a hospital for further treatment. Seven other people were treated on scene and stabilised before being transported by various ambulance services to nearby hospitals. https://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/1-dies-in-delivery-vehicle-accident-on-christmas-morning-20181225